      "message": "I explicitly don\u0027t want to support floats, since they introduce complications (like, what 1.5 * time.minute / time.hour should be: 1.5 or 1?).\n\nThe suggestion also allows \"int / duration\" which also doesn\u0027t make sense. And it doesn\u0027t handle \u0027side\u0027 correctly (\u0027xv\u0027 and \u0027yv\u0027 need to be swapped if it is starlark.Right). In the end the code won\u0027t be simpler.",
